<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17640728-1">
               <interp inst="t17640728-1" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17640728-1" type="year" value="1764"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17640728-1" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17640728"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17640728-1" type="date" value="17640728"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17640728-1-off1-c34" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640728-1-defend35 t17640728-1-off1 t17640728-1-verdict4"></join>
         
               <p>388. (L.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17640728-1-defend35" type="defendantName">
                     John 
                     Smith 
                  <interp inst="t17640728-1-defend35" type="surname" value="Smith"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-1-defend35" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-1-defend35" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t17640728-1-off1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17640728-1-off1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-1-off1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pettyLarceny"></interp>
               stealing a linen handkerchief, value 6 d.
            </rs> the property of 
               <persName id="t17640728-1-victim36" type="victimName">
                  John 
                  Bridge 
               <interp inst="t17640728-1-victim36" type="surname" value="Bridge"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-1-victim36" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-1-victim36" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640728-1-off1 t17640728-1-victim36"></join>
                  </persName>
             , <rs id="t17640728-1-cd2" type="crimeDate">July 11</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640728-1-off1 t17640728-1-cd2"></join>. ++</p>
               <p>John Bridge. I live with a woollen-draper without Aldgate. Coming from thence, on the 11th of this instant, at 9 at night, about four doors on this side of <placeName id="t17640728-1-crimeloc3">Aldgate</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17640728-1-crimeloc3" type="placeName" value="Aldgate"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17640728-1-crimeloc3" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640728-1-off1 t17640728-1-crimeloc3"></join>, I felt something at my pocket: I felt, and missed my handkerchief: I turned round immediately, and laid hold of the prisoner, and charged him with stealing it; he said he had it not. I held him by the collar, and in searching him, found my handkerchief rolled up under his waistcoat, upon his hip-bone.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I found it on the ground, and was unwilling to let him have it, till I found it to be his. I came from Bristol, to receive some money due to me from on board a man of war, and have been in London but six weeks.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17640728-1-verdict4" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17640728-1-verdict4" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>. <rs id="t17640728-1-punish5" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17640728-1-punish5" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640728-1-defend35 t17640728-1-punish5"></join>
               T
            </rs>.</p>
            </div1>
